<p><strong>Glintstone Staff</strong>&nbsp;is a basic&nbsp;<a class="wiki_link" title="Elden Ring Glintstone Staffs" href="/Glintstone+Staffs" target="">Glintstone Staff</a>&nbsp;in <a class="wiki_link" title="Elden Ring Wiki" href="/Elden+Ring+Wiki">Elden Ring</a>. The <strong>Glintstone Staff</strong>&nbsp;scales primarily with <a class="wiki_link" title="Elden Ring Strength" href="/Strength" target="">Strength</a> and <a class="wiki_link" title="Elden Ring Dexterity" href="/Dexterity" target="">Dexterity</a> and is a good <a class="wiki_link" title="Elden Ring Weapons" href="/Weapons" target="">Weapon</a> for Striking enemies within range and with the glintstone, is especially used to&nbsp;cast&nbsp;<a class="wiki_link" title="Elden Ring Sorceries" href="/Sorceries" target="">Sorceries</a>.</p> 
<p>&nbsp;&nbsp;</p> 
<div class="lineleft"> 
 <p><em>Staff with a glintstone embedded at the tip. A catalyst for casting sorceries.&nbsp;</em></p> 
 <p><em>Sorceries must be memorized first at a site of lost grace, and a staff must be equipped to cast them.</em></p> 
</div> 
<p>&nbsp;</p> 
<h3 class="bonfire">Where to Find Glintstone Staff in&nbsp;Elden Ring</h3> 
<p>The Glintstone Staff weapon can be found at the following location:</p> 
<ul> 
 <li>Starting Equipment for the <a class="wiki_link" title="Elden Ring Prisoner" href="/Prisoner" target="">Prisoner</a> Class</li> 
 <li>Has a chance to be dropped by&nbsp;<a class="wiki_link" title="Elden Ring Noble Sorcerer" href="/Noble+Sorcerer">Noble Sorcerers</a>&nbsp;at <a class="wiki_link" title="Elden Ring Caria Manor" href="/Caria+Manor" target="">Caria Manor</a>.</li> 
 <li>Drops from a lone Noble Sorcerer, south of the Waypoint Ruins (and west of a small collection of graves). Behind the large broken tower ruin where the&nbsp;<a class="wiki_link" title="Elden Ring Troll" href="/Troll">Troll</a>-pulled <a class="wiki_link" title="Elden Ring Carriage" href="/Carriage">Carriage's</a> caravan starts it's journey. (map co-ordinates are:&nbsp; -194.50781 : 113.69531 )</li> 
 <li>Early game, you can farm for this on the noble sorcerers Northeast of the Agheel Lake South grace in southern Limgrave. From where you enter <a class="wiki_link" title="Elden Ring Limgrave" href="/Limgrave" target="">Limgrave</a>, head Southeast and look for some stones you can use as steps to drop down without dying, they'll be close to the border of the lake. Cut around the bottom of the lake, avoiding the patrolling mercenary, and then cut Southeast across the field toward the road. You should see a the Agheel Lake South grace point on a little shelf below the road.&nbsp;From the grace, there are at least 4 noble sorcerers nearby, but 2 are easy to reach. Wait for the mercenary patrolling the road to ride by, then head across the road and left until you're climbing the slope. One sorcerer &amp; retinue will be coming down this slope from the camp above. After killing them, turn around, and there is another sorcerer &amp; retinue traveling down the road. You may want to wait for the mercenary to pass again, because he takes actual effort to fight (whereas the sorcerers have bad eyesight and go down quickly). Once you've killed and looted both groups, head back to the grace to rest, because it's a rare enough drop that it'll probably take you many resets to get.</li> 
</ul> 
<p>&nbsp;</p> 
<h3 class="bonfire">Elden Ring Glintstone Staff Notes &amp; Tips</h3> 
<ul> 
 <li>Weapon <a class="wiki_link" title="Elden Ring Skills" href="/Skills" target="">Skill</a>: No Skill</li> 
 <li>This weapon&nbsp;can't be enchanted with&nbsp;<a class="wiki_link" title="Elden Ring Magic" href="/Magic" target="">Magic</a>&nbsp;nor infused with&nbsp;<a class="wiki_link" title="Elden Ring Ashes of War" href="/Ashes+of+War" target="">Ashes of War</a>.</li> 
 <li><strong>Glintstone Staff</strong>&nbsp;can be upgraded by using&nbsp;<a class="wiki_link" title="Elden Ring Smithing Stones" href="/Smithing+Stones" target="">Smithing Stones</a></li> 
 <li>Sell Value:&nbsp;&nbsp;<img title="Runes" src="/file/Elden-Ring/er-runes-13.png" alt="er runes 13" width="18" height="18">&nbsp;100</li> 
 <li>Base drop rate is 2.04% (at 100 Discovery)</li> 
 <li>Other notes and player tips go here</li> 
</ul> 
<p>&nbsp;</p> 
<h3 class="bonfire">Moveset &amp; Videos in&nbsp;Elden Ring for&nbsp;Glintstone Staff</h3> 
<ul> 
 <li>Videos for the Glintstone Staff Coming Soon</li> 
</ul> 
<p>&nbsp;</p> 
<h3 class="bonfire">Glintstone Staff Upgrades in Elden Ring</h3> 
<p>Please see the&nbsp;<a class="wiki_link" title="Elden Ring Upgrades" href="/Upgrades" target="">Upgrades</a>&nbsp;page to understand the weapon bolstering process.</p> 
<p>Requires regular reinforcement&nbsp;with&nbsp;<a class="wiki_link" title="Elden Ring Smithing Stone (1)" href="/Smithing+Stone+(1)" target="">Smithing Stone [1]</a>,&nbsp;<a class="wiki_link" title="Elden Ring Smithing Stone (2)" href="/Smithing+Stone+(2)" target="">Smithing Stone [2]</a>,&nbsp;<a class="wiki_link" title="Elden Ring Smithing Stone (3)" href="/Smithing+Stone+(3)" target="">Smithing Stone [3]</a>,&nbsp;<a class="wiki_link" title="Elden Ring Smithing Stone (4)" href="/Smithing+Stone+(4)" target="">Smithing Stone [4]</a>,&nbsp;<a class="wiki_link" title="Elden Ring Smithing Stone (5)" href="/Smithing+Stone+(5)" target="">Smithing Stone [5]</a>,&nbsp;<a class="wiki_link" title="Elden Ring Smithing Stone (6)" href="/Smithing+Stone+(6)" target="">Smithing Stone [6]</a>,&nbsp;<a class="wiki_link" title="Elden Ring Smithing Stone (7)" href="/Smithing+Stone+(7)" target="">Smithing Stone [7]</a>,&nbsp;<a class="wiki_link" title="Elden Ring Smithing Stone (8)" href="/Smithing+Stone+(8)" target="">Smithing Stone [8]</a>, and&nbsp;<a class="wiki_link" title="Elden Ring Ancient Dragon Smithing Stone" href="/Ancient+Dragon+Smithing+Stone">Ancient Dragon Smithing Stone</a>.</p> 
<p>Sorcery Scaling is based on&nbsp;<em>Int</em>&nbsp;stat. The&nbsp;<em>Int</em>&nbsp;of the the character with the staff&nbsp;equipped at the time of posting the&nbsp;<span style="color: #00ffff;">Sor Scaling</span>&nbsp;is located in the&nbsp;(Int)&nbsp;to the right of the scaling amount. This will help to give a general idea of what staves are better at various&nbsp;<em>Int</em>&nbsp;levels until MAX is achieved.</p> 
<p>This upgrade can't be enchanted with&nbsp;<a class="wiki_link" title="Elden Ring Magic Spells" href="/Magic+Spells" target="">Magic</a>&nbsp;or boosted with&nbsp;<a class="wiki_link" title="Elden Ring Consumables" href="/Consumables" target="">Consumables</a>. <span style="color: #00ffff;">The Sorcery Scaling displayed on this table shows Minimum Requirement and Intelligence 80 as xx-yy.</span></p> 
